    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM AXLES: SPICER J400-S, W460-S - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="9">
            <title>INTER-AXLE DIFFERENTIAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place end yoke in a soft jawed vise. Use a torque wrench to remove input flange nut (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400421">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400421" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400421" filename="../figg14/G1400421.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 21. Remove Input Flange Nut</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove end yoke from inter-axle differential shaft using a suitable puller (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400422">Figure 22</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400422" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400422" filename="../figg14/G1400422.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 22. Remove End Yoke From Inter-Axle Differential Shaft</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift off inter-axle differential cover housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400423">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400423" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400423" filename="../figg14/G1400423.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 23. Lift Off Inter-Axle Differential Cover Housing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bearing cup and shims from inter-axle differential housing. Retain shims for
                    re-use when reassembling (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400424">Figure 24</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400424" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400424" filename="../figg14/G1400424.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 24. Remove Bearing Cups and Shims From Inter-Axle Differential Housing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove spiral snap ring, use a small bladed screwdriver. Insert tip into slot of snap
                    ring and lift away from case. Apply pressure under snap ring and rotate around case until snap ring
                    is free (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400425">Figure 25</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400425" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400425" filename="../figg14/G1400425.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 25. Remove Spiral Snap Ring</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove ball bearing from inter-axle differential case using suitable puller (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400426">Figure 26</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400426" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400426" filename="../figg14/G1400426.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 26. Remove Ball Bearing From Inter-Axle Differential Case</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Match mark differential case halves to assure correct alignment upon reassembly. Remove
                    differential case bolts and separate case halves (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400427">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400427" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400427" filename="../figg14/G1400427.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 27. Match Mark Differential Case Halves</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove pinion mates, front and rear side gears, cross shaft and thrust washers (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400428">Figure 28</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400428" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400428" filename="../figg14/G1400428.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 28. Remove Pinion Mates, Front and Rear Side Gears, Cross Shaft and Thrust Washers
                    </caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Side gear thrust washers are positioned on the front side gear only.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If tapered roller bearing is to be replaced, remove bearing using a suitable puller (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400429">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400429" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400429" filename="../figg14/G1400429.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 29. Remove Roller Bearing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
